owl:Ontology.dc:creator: C. Maria Keet
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: In the annotations for the entities, besides occasional comments, there is a list of terms as it is use in the covered conceptual data modelling languages, which is in the order of and format: UML v2.4.1 EER ORM

This is the OWLized version of the unifying metamodel for the static, structural components of UML class diagrams, EER, and ORM2, and their constraints.
The diagrammatic representation of the static structural components only, and their rationale, are described in the following two publications:
Keet, C.M., Fillottrani, P.R. Toward an ontology-driven unifying metamodel for UML Class Diagrams, EER, and ORM2. 32nd International Conference on Conceptual Modeling (ER'13). W. Ng, V.C. Storey, and J. Trujillo (Eds.). Springer LNCS 8217, 313-326. 11-13 November, 2013, Hong Kong.
Keet, C.M., Fillottrani, P.R. Structural entities of an ontology-driven unifying metamodel for UML, EER, and ORM2. 3rd International Conference on Model & Data Engineering (MEDI'13). A. Cuzzocrea and S. Maabout (Eds.) September 25-27, 2013, Amantea, Calabria, Italy. Springer LNCS 8216, 188-199.
A paper describing the full metamodel, including the constraints, is currently under review with an international journal

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: There is also a 'constrained with' in the metamodel that can be seen to be the inverse of declaredOn. We now use the inverse(declaredOn) for that to reduce a bit the number of object properties and gain some in reasoner performance.
Not very imaginative name, but it is for asserting that each wak object type must be related to a normal ('strong') one
Same story as with the declaredOn: also here one could choose to keep either identifies and identifiedBy. We chose the identifies, and avail of the other direciion by using inverse
The object subproperties of naryProperty are only here due to reifying ternaries and quaternary. Thus, they are NOT to be used for any other axiom than for said reification.
The metamodel also has participatesIn, which is replaced by inverse(participant); like with identifies and declaredOn
